This used to be an old school German restaurant that has been transformed into a Italian Steakhouse. They’ve kept some of the Kitchy German decorations, including fresh BBK on tap. This restaurant opened up on Thursday Dec 8th. Arturo, the owner and chef, has an extensive background in Italian fine dining. I brought my wife and two children to have dinner here on a Saturday evening. From the moment we walked in, the service was second to none all evening long. We ordered the pizza bread and fried calamari as appetizers and it was cooked to perfection. The minestrone soup and house salad wasn't anything to miss either. My wife had the shrimp risotto. My daughter had the filet mignon that was accompanied by broccoli sauteed in garlic. My son had the mostaccioli in a marinara sauce. I had the veal lemone. We also ordered the house potatoes to accompany our entrees. Everything was amazing! For dessert we ordered the lemon cake, tiramisu and spumoni ice cream which consisted of layers of pistachio, coconut, chocolate and strawberry. The dining rooms are spacious and the decor is charming. There is also a very nice size bar when you walk in with an extensive selection of drinks. There is a  large parking lot across the street from the restaurant  that they share with Kmart  so parking should never be an issue. I highly recommend everyone to make their way to the northwest side for fine Italian dining at an incredible price.

Folks DON’T WASTE your time and money here, Mirabell is the worst German joint in Chicago, no doubt. Please, don't go to this horrible stable with rude staff and bad quality food.  I do online marketing for restaurants and bars professionally, my opinion is right to the point.  They got no clue about service. My friend and I came in for a beer, the bar was packed, we got seated at a table and got 2 beers and an appetizer since we weren’t that hungry. Believe it or not, we were treated like TRASH by the waitress (about 65 y.o., red hair) throughout entire visit. She was all about “turning tables”, this did allow us to enjoy anything and we had the worst bar time ever!  The waitress wasn’t doing anything, the only guy who was, was her Latino busser. We took care of him since he deserved it, we also left a small tip for her because we had MISERABLE SERVICE.  Guess what, when we were walking out, she made a very funky face, didn’t say anything, only gave us a cheesy smile. When I am coming out of the restroom, the hostess comes up and tries to give me the tip back in front of people around saying:”here is your change, the tip is on me.”  What a rude stupid way to treat the customers! Now this story will go viral among multiple thousands of people I know and I don’t. The food is way too overpriced for this area and is of poor quality, they think they are in River North or are very desperate which makes them to cut on food quality and service level.  Staff is mostly unfriendly, rude, unprofessional, negative, and desperate.  Guys, don’t go to this stall and waste your time and money here. Instead, I would recommend Brauhaus (the owner Guenther still works there and takes care of his customers), Laschets in Irv.Pk. Rd. or Huettenbar (no food menu but great place) which is right across from Brauhaus in Lincoln Square.  To the owner of Mirabell I would recommend to hire young, positive and energetic wait staff that creates repetitive customers. What you have there now is mainly a bunch of folks who got no clue about service and restaurant business. Please, stay in business and look into your company’s service standards. This is not the only 1 star review you have, if bad stories like this at Mirabell will continue going viral, you won’t be able to stay in business. Thanks and Best of luck.
